      ],
      "text": "Arif was planning a coup against Prime Minister Qasim, who may have learned of Arif's plans and moved first.\n\nNasir has indicated his support of Arif and will probably be alarmed that he is apparently losing ground. He may contend that the removal of Arif, whom he claims to be the only Iraqi capable of combating Communist influence, is a victory for the pro-Soviet and anti-UAR faction. This claim could serve Nasir as an excuse for active interference in Iraqi affairs.",
